{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/sand_strand", "parent": "grains"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Granular Strand"], "extent": [42, 62]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fills grains along the edges of polygons, creating a beaded wire effect."], "extent": [62, 143]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [143, 158], "body": [{"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [158, 165], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This tool is a technical demo of alternate uses for the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " tool."], "extent": [165, 276]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool fills grains along the edges of polygons, creating a beaded wire effect. Similar to the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/granularsheet", "type": "link", "text": ["Granular Sheet"], "fullpath": "/shelf/granularsheet"}, " tool, the particles are densely packed to give some bend resistance. The particles are evenly spaced and very tightly constrained. This could be used for creating things like stacked necklaces, nets, or chains."], "extent": [276, 624]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool can be thought of as a simple wire solver. It results in wire-like behavior because there are no collisions between particles since they are all right next to each other and constrained. An advantage of using this tool for simple strand simulations is that it\u2019s very stable and faster in certain instances."], "extent": [624, 942]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [942, 947], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["To pin a PBD simulation, make sure you set the mass of the particles to 0."], "extent": [947, 1040]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Granular Strand"], "extent": [1040, 1080], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the object to convert to a Granular Strand."], "extent": [1080, 1143]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/sand_strand", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/sand_strand"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["Granular Strand"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Grains"]}, " tab."], "extent": [1143, 1253]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/granularstrand.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1253, 1303]}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/popgrains", "type": "link", "text": ["POP Grains"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/popgrains"}, " help."], "extent": [1303, 1386]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1386, 1392], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["There is no twist when using this tool, unlike the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/wiresolver", "type": "link", "text": ["wire solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/wiresolver"}, " can do with hair."], "extent": [1392, 1502]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "title": ["Granular Strand"], "summary": ["Fills grains along the edges of polygons, creating a beaded wire effect."]}